I'm going to make a suggestion here... I'm not perfectly happy with how you turned this into foam... Use bromelain. A natural enzyme found in pineapple, that will reduce the proteins in meat to... well, almost a liquid texture to begin with. what you've done here is just make the particle size small enough to simulate a whipped texture, but it's not truly liquid meat. Using bromelain WILL make liquid meat.

Try it again with bromelain and letting it sit for several days, then foaming it, and cooking it. THEN I'll believe it... Also before you make it into foam, dry it out a bit, to remove some of the water, so it doesn't have that same watered down flavour.
